            "question": "A fair coin is tossed 9 times. What is the probability of getting exactly 7 heads?",
            "difficulty": "hard",
            "hasDiagram": false,
            "options": {
                "A": "36.0/2^9",
                "B": "9/2^9",
                "C": "1/2^9",
                "D": "72/2^9"
            },
            "answer": "A",
            "hint": "Use Binomial distribution: nCr * (1/2)^r * (1/2)^(n-r)",
            "solution": "P(X=7) = 9C7 * (1/2)^n = 36.0/2^9.",
            "id": 4
